Oct 2015, Bangalore.

We are happy to announce Caring Friends-Nature Forever Society Conservation Research Fellowship.

Aims to fund individuals who want to conduct research on lesser known & non-glamorous species, habitats, innovations and environment conservation issues for which funding is difficult or scarce, the funding will be available for a maximum of 3 years and should fit the criteria.

The research should be original well defined and have measurable indicators. It can cover any species of flora or fauna from ants to habitats which are lesser explored.

Individuals can be professional researchers or non-professionals from any field or profession.

An annual fellowship of Rs.60, 000/- will be offered to five individuals.

For applications and other details write or call to mohammed@natureforever.org | 9420001820 for more details
